What is a server?

A server is a computer or software program that is often designed to run 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.
It provides data, resources, or services to other computers called “clients” within a computer network.



What is the role of the domain name?

The main purpose of a domain name is to provide users with an address that is easier to remember than an IP address.



What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?

The “www.” subdomain often points to the main domain, so it uses a CNAME record.



What is the role of the web server?

The role of the web server is to deliver a web page to the user (HTML, CSS, JavaScript).



What is the role of the application server?

The role of the application server is that host application or software that executes application/business logic,
processes user requests and and returns dynamic responses.



What is the role of the database?

The role of a database is to store, organize, manage data.



What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website?

Web servers use the HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) to communicate.



